&lt;/h2>&lt;h1 id="introduzione">Introduzione
&lt;/h1>&lt;p>Volevo un server multimediale leggero, efficiente e open-source per gestire la mia libreria di film e serie TV.
Ho scelto Jellyfin perché offre ottime funzionalità senza richiedere licenze a pagamento.
In questo articolo, spiegherò come ho configurato il mio server usando un Raspberry Pi 4.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/demone.jpg"
width="1800"
height="2512"
srcset="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/demone_hu_f15344cdeae4b749.jpg 480w, https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/demone_hu_67fa859220d9ed4d.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="pi4"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="71"
data-flex-basis="171px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/alfa.jpg"
width="1800"
height="2520"
srcset="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/alfa_hu_3f9179e937fd151.jpg 480w, https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/alfa_hu_e57a4f89e7dbde37.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="pi4"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="71"
data-flex-basis="171px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="hardware-utilizzato">Hardware utilizzato
&lt;/h1>&lt;p>• Raspberry Pi 4B (4GB di RAM)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>• MicroSD (per il sistema operativo)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>• HDD esterno da 2TB (per i file multimediali) (facoltativo)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>• Mini Tower NAS kit ZP-0130 (facoltativo)&lt;/p>
&lt;h1 id="installazione-del-sistema-operativo">Installazione del sistema operativo
&lt;/h1>&lt;p>Per mantenere il sistema il più leggero e performante possibile, ho scelto di installare Raspberry Pi OS Lite. Questa versione senza interfaccia grafica consente di gestire il server in modo efficiente tramite SSH, senza caricare risorse inutili.
Tuttavia, se preferisci un&amp;rsquo;interfaccia grafica, puoi optare per la versione Raspberry Pi OS con Desktop, che offre un ambiente grafico completo, perfetto se desideri un&amp;rsquo;esperienza più interattiva e visiva.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Ho scaricato l&amp;rsquo;ultima versione di Raspberry Pi OS Lite dal sito ufficiale.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Ho usato Raspberry Pi Imager per scrivere l&amp;rsquo;immagine sulla microSD.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Dopo aver configurato la rete direttamente dal Raspberry Pi collegato a uno schermo e a una tastiera, ed aver aggiornato il sistema con:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo apt update &lt;span class="o">&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span> sudo apt upgrade -y
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="installazione-di-docker">Installazione di Docker
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Per migliorare la gestione delle applicazioni, ho deciso di installare Docker sul Raspberry Pi.
Ora puoi procedere con l&amp;rsquo;installazione di Docker e Docker Compose.
Aggiunta del repository Docker:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nb">printf&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s1">&amp;#39;%s\n&amp;#39;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;deb https://download.docker.com/linux/debian bullseye stable&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">|&lt;/span> sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker-ce.list
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Importazione della chiave GPG ufficiale:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/debian/gpg &lt;span class="p">|&lt;/span> sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/docker-ce-archive-keyring.gpg
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Installazione di Docker:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo apt-get update
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="installazione-e-configurazione-di-portainer">Installazione e configurazione di Portainer
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/cont.jpg"
width="3811"
height="1870"
srcset="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/cont_hu_2ac30f3ddee86a24.jpg 480w, https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/cont_hu_880973dbce9bd298.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="portainer"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="203"
data-flex-basis="489px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Per semplificare la gestione dei container, ho installato Portainer, un&amp;rsquo;interfaccia grafica per Docker.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Creazione del volume per i dati di Portainer:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo docker volume create portainer_data
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Avvio del container Portainer:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -p 9443:9443 --name portainer --restart&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>always &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -v portainer_data:/data portainer/portainer-ce:2.21.4
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/dash.jpg"
width="3831"
height="1882"
srcset="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/dash_hu_1f655898f4ec3166.jpg 480w, https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/dash_hu_cda9486fa413a772.jpg 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="portainer"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="203"
data-flex-basis="488px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="installazione-e-configurazione-di-jellyfin">Installazione e configurazione di Jellyfin
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Per configurare Jellyfin come server multimediale, ho seguito questi passaggi:&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Creazione delle cartelle necessarie
Prima di avviare il container, ho creato le seguenti cartelle per la configurazione, la cache e i media:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">mkdir -p ~/jellyfin_config
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">mkdir -p ~/jellyfin_cache
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">mkdir -p ~/media
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="scaricamento-e-avvio-del-container-jellyfin">Scaricamento e Avvio del Container Jellyfin
&lt;/h2>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">4
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">5
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">6
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">7
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">8
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">docker run -d &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> --name jellyfin &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -p 8096:8096 &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -v ~/docker_apps/jellyfin/config:/config &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -v ~/docker_apps/jellyfin/cache:/cache &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> -v ~/docker_apps/media:/media &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> --restart always &lt;span class="se">\
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="se">&lt;/span> jellyfin/jellyfin
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="esempio-dei-miei-container-docker">Esempio dei miei container Docker
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://wifi-revenge.github.io/blog/p/server-con-raspberry-pi-e-jellyfin/ps.jpg"
